# VS Code Local Extensions Configuration
# ========================================
# 
# This project stores VS Code extensions locally instead of C:\Users\<username>\.vscode\extensions
#
# HOW TO USE:
# -----------
# Instead of opening VS Code normally, use one of these methods:
#
# Method 1: Double-click start-vscode.bat
# Method 2: Run in PowerShell: .\start-vscode.ps1
# Method 3: Run in terminal:
#           code --extensions-dir ".vscode-extensions" "d:\ML project\house-price-predictor"
#
# INSTALLING EXTENSIONS:
# ----------------------
# After launching VS Code with the script above, install extensions normally.
# They will be saved to: .vscode-extensions\ folder in this project
#
# BENEFITS:
# ---------
# 1. Extensions are portable with your project
# 2. Saves space on C: drive
# 3. Different projects can have different extensions
# 4. Easy to backup/restore
#
# EXTENSIONS DIRECTORY:
VSCODE_EXTENSIONS_DIR=.vscode-extensions

# Backend Configuration
FLASK_APP=backend/app.py
FLASK_ENV=development
FLASK_DEBUG=1
FLASK_PORT=5000
FLASK_HOST=127.0.0.1

# Frontend Configuration  
VITE_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:5000
VITE_PORT=5173

# Python Environment
PYTHONPATH=backend
